          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>Yiddish</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Pa</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi>
                                        </add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                                        <date>July 20, 1849</date>
                                        <add>?</add>
                              </p>
                              <p>Honored Sir:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Since I have not received a definite<lb/> answer
                                        from <placeName>Germany</placeName> about the Torahs,<lb/>
                                        and you may not obtain everything just<lb/> as you wish it,
                                        I permit myself to write<lb/> to you again. I assure you
                                        that this<lb/> copy is excellent and perfect, in spite<lb/>
                                        of the fact that it is 28 inches long. The<lb/> writing in
                                        it is handsome and clear—not<lb/> too difficult. The columns
                                        are close to-<lb/>gether, so that it is not too heavy.
                                        I<lb/> shall also lower the price in view of<lb/> cash
                                        payment. Should you have no need<lb/> for it, I beg of you
                                        to include the following<lb/> advertisement in the
                                        “Occident”: Three<lb/> hundred and 60 catalogues will
                                        probably<lb/> arrive into your hands on
                                                  <date>Wednesday</date><lb/> by express. If
                                        extraordinary circum-<lb/>stances hinder me in this the
                                        matter<lb/> will rest 'till next month, <del>for the
                                                  follow-</del><lb/>
                                        <persName>Frank's</persName> prayer book will not come
                                        up<lb/> to yours either in completeness or in<lb/> beauty or
                                        in translation, but it will be<lb/> sold, for our brothers
                                        for the most<lb/> part do not require all this. They<lb/>
                                        want a prayer book with English more<lb/> as a matter of
                                        vanity than as a matter<lb/> of necessity, and they
                                        therefore buy</p>
                              <p rend="Written in margin next to last 5 lines">Note this</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>the cheapest. With regard to <persName>Dr.
                                                  Wort-<lb/>mann's</persName> affair, I received the
                                        enclosed.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">If several subscribers could be<lb/> obtained, for
                                        your writings, it could only<lb/> be for the
                                                  <date>July</date> number and semi-annual<lb/>
                                        subscriptions. More than $1.50 could not<lb/> be obtained
                                        from anyone and that with<lb/> difficulty. I should have
                                        done it even<lb/> without your request.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I hardly believe I shall be able to do<lb/> more
                                        for you. The fault is not mine.<lb/> That I tell you the
                                        truth, you will soon<lb/> discover.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Respectfully,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <persName role="author">Isidore Busch</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
